  "title": "Spa Therapist",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Experience:</strong> Proven experience as a spa or beauty therapist is often required.</li><li><strong>Licensing:</strong> State-specific licensing for massage therapy and/or cosmetology/aesthetics is typically necessary.</li><li><strong>Technical skills:</strong> Proficiency in various massage techniques, skincare, and other spa treatments.</li><li><strong>Soft skills:</strong> Excellent communication, interpersonal, and customer service skills are crucial.</li><li><strong>Knowledge:</strong> A solid understanding of anatomy, physiology, and different spa products and their uses is essential.</li><li><strong>Certifications:</strong> CPR and First Aid certifications are often advantageous.</li><li><strong>Physical requirements:</strong> Ability to stand for extended periods and perform physical tasks.</li></ul>",
